We recommend that the City Mayor, the HRMO and the City Accountant:
Attach/Submit the duly certified copy of the Job Order Contracts/Service Contracts by the HRMO with statement of the expected work or output;
Require each payee to prepare the accomplishment report duly verified and accepted by the immediate supervisor;
Set up bundy clock/biometric to record the time/man-hours rendered; and
Fill up existing vacant plantilla positions which are vital in the delivery of basic services which would lessen the number of hired job order workers.

Consider the following courses of action:
Ensure that gender development is mainstreamed in the local policy-making, planning, programming and budgeting by strictly implementing the GAD Focal Point System (GFPS) mechanism and that this GFPS must be fully functional by having fully functional members that have the capacity to influence and promote gender mainstreaming;
Update its gender audit and analysis of the City’s policies, programs, services and undertake an analysis of its sex-disaggregated data to provide inputs to the formulation of a GAD Code.  Prioritize the formulation of the GAD Code to provide guidance to planning, program/ project identification and policy-making;
Develop GAD database containing information about gender mainstreaming; and 
Direct the Accounting Department to maintain a separate subsidiary ledger for GAD expenditures that will facilitate reporting of fund utilization and validation thereof.

Require the Human Resource Officer to formulate written policies and guidelines on the procurement of JO services and categorically establish rights and obligations of the City and JO personnel and minimize the risk of hiring unqualified and/or unnecessary JO personnel, by considering the following:
Appropriate approved documents indicating the number of personnel involved and their corresponding rates/salary; and schedule of work and places of assignment or station;
The scaled floor plans of the building and other area’s covered by the service contract (for janitorial services);
Approved documents indicating the minimum requirements of the agency on the number of security personnel to be involved in the project (for security service contract);
The population of the agency where the services are rendered (for security service contract);
Detailed description of the maintenance services to be rendered or activities to be performed (for maintenance service contracts).

Ensure that the hiring of JO personnel be made an integral part of the LGU’s procurement and budget planning, taking into consideration the need of each department/office, the estimated number of JOs to be hired and their wages and qualifications.
